You could check
your e-mail anywhere.

14:33.956 --> 14:35.791
Uh, yeah, e-mail, but this is g-mail.

14:36.083 --> 14:37.459
Down here on the third floor
set it up for me,

14:37.751 --> 14:39.503
and then when we moved
to the fourth,

14:39.587 --> 14:41.839
I was like, screw it,
I'll just come down here to check it,

14:41.922 --> 14:43.757
'cause I don't want wires
going everywhere.

14:43.841 --> 14:45.175
You can use your phone for that.

14:45.259 --> 14:46.760
Yeah, and I could use a pigeon.

14:47.177 --> 14:50.472
But for this particular task,
I've chosen e-mail.

14:51.140 --> 14:53.475
Anyway, I sent my résumé out,

14:53.642 --> 14:56.061
and the only firm that's gotten back to me

14:56.145 --> 14:57.897
is the gang over at Mailer Daemon.

14:58.063 --> 15:00.524
Aw, damn it! God, missed him again.

15:00.691 --> 15:02.276
It seems like they write me back

15:02.359 --> 15:04.153
every time I step away
from this thing.

15:04.445 --> 15:06.071
Well, on the other hand,
this is on them,

15:06.155 --> 15:09.992
'cause I made it clear that I was looking
for a three-day-a-week president job,

15:10.075 --> 15:12.369
and why... why...

15:14.496 --> 15:18.500
Why-why... when...

15:18.584 --> 15:20.961
when... what kind of... when... what...?

15:21.837 --> 15:24.006
You're looking for a president job?

15:27.176 --> 15:30.304
- I'll be damned, it is a he.
- Who e-mails back...

15:30.387 --> 15:32.514
What? At Wednesday at nap?

15:32.598 --> 15:33.849
Hey, Gob, we want to beat

15:33.933 --> 15:35.267
Mailer Daemon to the punch.

15:35.351 --> 15:37.603
Come to Fakeblock. Be <i>our </i> president.

15:37.686 --> 15:39.730
You won't need
to get your e-mail redelivered.

15:39.813 --> 15:41.732
Yeah. You already know the lay
of the office.

15:41.815 --> 15:43.692
You won't have to learn new snacks.

15:44.026 --> 15:45.444
And everybody knows you,

15:45.527 --> 15:47.321
so there won't be
gaining everyone's respect.

15:47.404 --> 15:49.114
And the best part is,
you get paid in stock.

15:49.448 --> 15:51.492
Right. Money never has to change hands.

15:53.744 --> 15:54.912
I'm listening.

15:56.497 --> 15:58.374
- That's it. We're done talking.
- Mm-hmm.

15:59.541 --> 16:00.626
Can I get back to you?

16:00.960 --> 16:02.252
- Yeah.
- I'm in.

16:02.962 --> 16:04.797
- Great!
- Well, looks like

16:04.880 --> 16:07.049
I'm gonna need
that office space after all.

16:07.132 --> 16:10.636
This is not gonna be
an easy conversation.

16:10.719 --> 16:13.055
But mostly thankful
for the one man

16:13.138 --> 16:14.098
who made this all possible.

16:14.264 --> 16:17.434
Who took this ragtag,
talented troupe of a family

16:17.518 --> 16:19.269
and... and put a roof
over their head,

16:19.728 --> 16:22.314
Jeff in their mouth,
and gave us the dignity

16:22.398 --> 16:25.109
to move as we will
after work hours.

16:25.192 --> 16:27.236
To my brother-in-law Gob.

16:27.319 --> 16:28.362
Long may...

16:29.488 --> 16:31.073
I need you guys out of here.

16:31.448 --> 16:32.741
And we're on the move again.

16:32.825 --> 16:34.076
I don't want to go back
to living in that attic.

16:34.159 --> 16:36.453
And the heat made me like,
"What's happening? Who are you?"

16:36.745 --> 16:38.414
- We'll figure something out, Murphybrown.
- Okay, I hate to be

16:38.497 --> 16:40.416
the one to suggest it,
but I know about a tent city.

16:40.499 --> 16:42.418
Well, there you go.
We're down a rung,

16:42.501 --> 16:44.086
but we're down a rung together.

16:44.420 --> 16:46.588
Thanks, guys.
My first day as president,

16:46.672 --> 16:48.424
and kicking people out makes it...

16:48.507 --> 16:50.884
- makes it seem real.
- Oh, Gob. Something came for you.

16:51.301 --> 16:52.261
Hmm.

16:54.263 --> 16:56.181
Powerful Gay Tastemakers?

16:56.682 --> 16:57.683
The Gay Mafia.

16:58.100 --> 17:00.269
- What?
- That's the Gay Mafia.

17:00.352 --> 17:01.770
Surely you've heard of them.

17:01.854 --> 17:03.981
Very flattering. That's the real deal.

17:05.816 --> 17:08.152
I wonder if this is from Tony.

17:08.444 --> 17:10.779
Maybe this is how
he's trying to reach out to me.

17:10.863 --> 17:13.365
Wow. So I guess...

17:13.866 --> 17:16.076
I guess sometimes
things do work out, after all.

17:17.117 --> 17:19.288
- So we can stay?
- No.

17:19.747 --> 17:20.622
For me.

17:21.665 --> 17:23.333
Things work out for me.

17:23.415 --> 17:25.711
<i>And while things</i>
<i>were working out for Gob,</i>

17:25.961 --> 17:28.672
<i>upstairs,
things were not working out so well</i>

17:28.756 --> 17:31.300
<i>- for Michael.</i>
- Remember, Mom doesn't want me

17:31.383 --> 17:33.510
to see the file, so I guess
this is what you'd call a...

17:33.677 --> 17:36.472
- Don't tell Gangee.
- You see the fun we have?

17:36.972 --> 17:39.141
I know you do.
Come on, the printer's in here.

17:39.224 --> 17:41.935
So, it is a three-dimensional printer,
but I've just let it go all day.

17:44.229 --> 17:45.606
What is this?

17:45.689 --> 17:47.149
Is this the printer
you sent the file to?

17:47.983 --> 17:50.027
Uh, yeah. Yeah, yeah. I think so.

17:50.110 --> 17:52.237
The... the file that was labeled
"Gated Community."

17:55.074 --> 17:57.576
I think that this is

17:58.077 --> 18:01.038
a map that they did not want me to see.

18:01.830 --> 18:04.958
It looks like a wall on the border, but...

18:05.667 --> 18:07.044
made out of teeth?

18:07.920 --> 18:11.924
She's crazy. She's totally crazy.

18:12.132 --> 18:13.717
That might be a setting
in the printer.

18:13.801 --> 18:15.761
Let me see what we have here.
Yeah. See?

18:15.844 --> 18:17.930
Right here. You have to uncheck
"Presume Teeth."

18:18.013 --> 18:19.431
This is what they need me
to find money for.

18:19.515 --> 18:21.016
This is their secret project, huh?

18:21.100 --> 18:23.560
Well, there's only one way
to find out for sure.

18:23.727 --> 18:24.937
Uncheck "Presume Teeth."

18:25.020 --> 18:26.396
And print again.

18:27.189 --> 18:28.941
<i>And as they went to do so,</i>

18:29.149 --> 18:31.318
<i>Gob went to meet with the Gay Mafia,</i>

18:31.819 --> 18:35.197
<i>hoping to run into
his old friend Tony Wonder.</i>

18:35.697 --> 18:37.866
Are there any tastemakers?

18:41.036 --> 18:42.121
Tastemakers?

18:42.204 --> 18:45.916
You sold a French Regency armoire,
and you don't think I'm gonna hear?

18:46.083 --> 18:48.168
